              <li><span class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Dividend Investing:</span>
                Focusing on stocks of mature, stable companies that consistently
                pay out a portion of their profits to shareholders.</li>
              <li><span class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Bond Laddering:</span>
                Investing in a series of bonds with staggered maturity dates to
                provide regular income streams and manage interest rate risk.</li>
              <li><span class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Real Estate
                  Investment Trusts (REITs):</span>
                Investing in companies that own, operate, or finance
                income-producing real estate, distributing a significant portion
                of their income to shareholders.</li>
              <li><span class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Fixed Income
                  Securities:</span>
                Investing in government or corporate bonds that pay regular
                interest payments.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-base text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">This strategy
              often appeals to retirees or those looking to create a reliable
              stream of supplemental income, typically involving assets with
              lower volatility than growth stocks.</p>
