            <p class="text-base text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">Dollar-Cost
              Averaging (DCA) is a strategy where you invest a fixed amount of
              money at regular intervals, regardless of the asset's price. This
              approach automatically buys more shares when prices are low and
              fewer shares when prices are high, potentially reducing the
              overall average cost per share over time. DCA is particularly
              effective for:</p>
            <ul
              class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-400 text-base space-y-2"
            >
              <li><span class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Reducing Market
                  Timing Risk:</span>
                You don't need to predict market highs or lows.</li>
              <li><span class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Disciplined
                  Investing:</span>
                Encourages regular contributions, building long-term habits.</li>
              <li><span class="font-semibold text-slate-200">Mitigating
                  Volatility:</span>
                Spreads out your purchase prices, potentially smoothing out
                returns during volatile periods.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-base text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">DCA is a
              fantastic strategy for passive investors who prioritize
              consistency and want to build wealth gradually without the stress
              of constant market monitoring.</p>
